## Inquiry Objects

& [FermatPrimeSeedSet] is the initial local focus
  + [members] is 3, 5, 17, 257, 65537
  + [identity_rule] is p = 2^(2^n) + 1 for n = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 with p prime
  + [inspection_question] is what constraints become visible when prime identity is anchored by a power-of-two exponent tower

& [Prime641] is correlated periphery
  + [known_surface] is a prime related to the next Fermat-number boundary
  + [inspection_question] is whether 641 belongs to the local Fermat-prime identity or to a distinct factor-boundary identity

& [NearbyOddPrimeFamilies] is an immediate periphery set
  + [candidate_families] is Mersenne primes, Proth primes, Pierpont primes, Sophie Germain primes, safe primes, Wieferich primes, and irregular primes
  + [inspection_question] is which nearby families share surface shape, which share causal arithmetic constraints, and which merely resemble the seed focus

